{"id":"5e9c30539b6559241525db44","artists":["5e9b69177a1236eccfeb2293"],"title":"Introducing: Little Kid","content":"<p><a rel=\"attachment wp-att-8524\" href=\"https://admin.</p><p>crackintheroad.com/music/8492-introducing-little-kid/attachment/littlekid\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-8524\" title=\"littlekid\" src=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/uploads/2011/06/littlekid.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"673\" srcset=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/06/littlekid.jpg 650w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/06/littlekid-260x269.jpg 260w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/06/littlekid-640x662.jpg 640w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/06/littlekid-165x170.jpg 165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" /></a></p>\n<p>‘Lo-Fi’ music has became a bit of a dirty word. The attitude of ‘sticking a bit of reverb on it and hoping for the best’ has taken over, leaving a lot of contemporary music coming across as fashion music and little else. <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/#!/pages/Little-Kid/\"><strong>Little Kid</strong></a> does not fall into that trap. Sure his music could be described as Lo-Fi, it is made on a 4-track after all, but beneath the crackles and hisses are beautifully constructed folk numbers, with the background noises only adding to the lonely and introspective atmosphere. He has a 10 song album up for free download, be a star and download it now.</p>\n<p><iframe width=\"400\" height=\"100\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; width: 400px; height: 100px;\" src=\"https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/v=2/album=1059331658/size=venti/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/\" allowtransparency=\"true\" frameborder=\"0\"><a href=\"https://littlekid.bandcamp.com/album/logic-songs\">Logic Songs by Little Kid</a></iframe></p>\n","slug":"8492-introducing-little-kid","category":"music","date":1307883779000,"wpid":8492,"isSticky":false,"featured_image":{"width":650,"height":673,"src":"2011/06/littlekid.j